# Session Bootstrap

Before proposing any implementation plan, always read:
- `README.md`
- `AGENTS.md`
- `memory/CONVERSATION_MEMORY.md`
- `memory/daily/` today and yesterday notes if they exist
- `TASKS.md`
- `WORKLOG.md`
- `lobster-factory/docs/LOBSTER_FACTORY_MASTER_CHECKLIST.md` (if exists)
- `lobster-factory/docs/LOBSTER_FACTORY_COMPLETION_PLAN_V2.md` (if exists)

If those files are not found in the current opened folder, retry under `agency-os/`
with the same filenames before declaring context missing.

At the beginning of every new conversation, output this exact structure:

- Yesterday Recap:
  - Completed
  - Pending
  - Risks/Blockers
- Today Plan:
  - Priority 1
  - Priority 2
  - Priority 3
- Confirm:
  - "今天先做哪一項？"

If prior context is missing, explicitly say "無法可靠讀取昨日脈絡" and ask
the user for a one-line recap before continuing.

If files are missing, create them using project templates before proceeding.

For any code/doc change request, first read the full target file and all directly
related source-of-truth files. Before finalizing, do a conflict pass to detect:
- duplicate or contradictory instructions
- stale path assumptions (`D:\Work` vs `<WORK_ROOT>` vs relative paths)
- mismatched status between checklist/task/worklog/memory
